{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862649037,"sessionID":"ses_28656b9f8ffeB7yx0UgDfwYzlW","part":{"id":"prt_d79a98326001vvgE9fFRxB6hRW","messageID":"msg_d79a96c04001knvCmFzB2BP8nK","sessionID":"ses_28656b9f8ffeB7yx0UgDfwYzlW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010: Router дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ - Task Checklist\n2: \n3: > **AR ID:** AR-010  \n4: > **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n5: > **Language:** Go  \n6: > **Size:** M  \n7: > **Stage:** ST-3 completed  \n8: > **Depends on:** AR-003 (client-go), AR-009 (Router HTTP Core)\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## Task 1: Create Session Types and Constants\n13: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_types.go` with core type definitions\n14: \n15: - [ ] Create `session_types.go` file\n16: - [ ] Define `SessionStatus` string type with constants:\n17:   - `SessionStatusPending`, `SessionStatusActive`, `SessionStatusExpiring`, `SessionStatusTerminated`\n18: - [ ] Define `SessionInfo` struct with fields: SessionID, SandboxID, RuntimeRef, Status, CreatedAt, LastActivity, ExpiresAt, EntryPoints\n19: - [ ] Define `RuntimeReference` struct with fields: Kind, Name, Namespace\n20: - [ ] Define `SessionFilter` struct with fields: Status, RuntimeKind, Namespace, Before\n21: - [ ] Define `SessionConfig` struct with fields: DefaultTTL, MaxTTL, CleanupInterval, ActivityTimeout\n22: - [ ] Define `EndpointEntry` struct with fields: SessionID, SandboxID, Endpoint, LastUsed, Healthy\n23: - [ ] Add default constants: DefaultSessionTTL (30m), MaxSessionTTL (24h), DefaultCleanupInterval (5m), DefaultActivityTimeout (30m)\n24: - [ ] Add JSON tags and documentation comments\n25: - [ ] Write unit tests verifying type definitions\n26: \n27: **Verification Command:**\n28: ```bash\n29: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionTypes\" && \\\n30: grep -E \"SessionStatus|SessionInfo|RuntimeReference\" pkg/router/session_types.go\n31: ```\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Task 2: Create Session Error Types\n36: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_errors.go` with error definitions\n37: \n38: - [ ] Create `session_errors.go` file\n39: - [ ] Define `SessionError` struct with Code, Message, Cause fields\n40: - [ ] Implement `Error() string` method\n41: - [ ] Implement `Unwrap() error` method\n42: - [ ] Define sentinel errors:\n43:   - `ErrSessionNotFound` (code: SESSION_NOT_FOUND)\n44:   - `ErrSessionExpired` (code: SESSION_EXPIRED)\n45:   - `ErrRuntimeNotFound` (code: RUNTIME_NOT_FOUND)\n46:   - `ErrSandboxCreateFailed` (code: SANDBOX_CREATE_FAILED)\n47:   - `ErrInvalidSessionID` (code: INVALID_SESSION_ID)\n48:   - `ErrSessionConflict` (code: SESSION_CONFLICT)\n49:   - `ErrSessionStoreUnavailable` (code: STORE_UNAVAILABLE)\n50: - [ ] Write unit tests verifying error creation and unwrapping\n51: \n52: **Verification Command:**\n53: ```bash\n54: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionError\" && \\\n55: grep \"ErrSessionNotFound\\|ErrSessionExpired\" pkg/router/session_errors.go\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## Task 3: Create Session Manager Interface\n61: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_manager.go` with interface definition\n62: \n63: - [ ] Create `session_manager.go` file\n64: - [ ] Define `SessionManager` interface with methods:\n65:   - `Resolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, runtimeRef RuntimeReference, createIfMissing bool) (*SessionInfo, error)`\n66:   - `Create(ctx context.Context, runtimeRef RuntimeReference) (*SessionInfo, error)`\n67:   - `Refresh(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n68:   - `Terminate(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n69:   - `Get(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionInfo, error)`\n70:   - `ListActive(ctx context.Context, filter SessionFilter) ([]*SessionInfo, error)`\n71:   - `StartLifecycleManager(stopCh <-chan struct{})`\n72: - [ ] Define `sessionManager` struct with fields: store, k8sClient, workloadMgrAddr, httpClient, config, metrics, affinityRouter\n73: - [ ] Implement `NewSessionManager(store, k8sClient, config) SessionManager` constructor\n74: - [ ] Write unit tests for interface compliance\n75: \n76: **Verification Command:**\n77: ```bash\n78: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManagerInterface\" && \\\n79: grep -E \"type SessionManager interface|func NewSessionManager\" pkg/router/session_manager.go\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Task 4: Implement Session Resolution Logic\n85: **Verifiable Output:** SessionManager.Resolve method handles all resolution scenarios\n86: \n87: - [ ] Implement `Resolve()` method:\n88:   - If sessionID empty and createIfMissing=true, create new session\n89:   - Query session store by ID\n90:   - If found, update activity timestamp and return SessionInfo\n91:   - If not found, check if K8s resource exists via k8sClient\n92:   - If resource exists and createIfMissing, create new session\n93:   - If resource not found, return ErrRuntimeNotFound\n94: - [ ] Implement session validation (check expiration)\n95: - [ ] Add metrics recording for resolution duration and cache hits\n96: - [ ] Write unit tests for all resolution scenarios:\n97:   - Existing session found in store\n98:   - Session not found, K8s resource exists, create new\n99:   - Session not found, K8s resource not found\n100:   - Empty session ID with createIfMissing\n101:   - Expired session handling\n102: \n103: **Verification Command:**\n104: ```bash\n105: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManager_Resolve\"\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## Task 5: Implement Session Creation\n111: **Verifiable Output:** SessionManager.Create creates sessions via Workload Manager\n112: \n113: - [ ] Implement `Create()` method:\n114:   - Generate UUID v4 session ID\n115:   - Build Workload Manager request endpoint (`/v1/{kind}`)\n116:   - Call Workload Manager to create sandbox\n117:   - Wait for sandbox ready status (with timeout)\n118:   - Build SessionInfo from response\n119:   - Store session in session store with TTL\n120:   - Register session in affinity router\n121:   - Record metrics\n122: - [ ] Implement `mapKindToEndpoint()` helper\n123: - [ ] Implement `callWorkloadManager()` HTTP client method\n124: - [ ] Write unit tests with mock Workload Manager:\n125:   - Successful AgentRuntime session creation\n126:   - Successful CodeInterpreter session creation\n127:   - Workload Manager failure handling\n128:   - Sandbox timeout handling\n129: \n130: **Verification Command:**\n131: ```bash\n132: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManager_Create\"\n133: ```\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## Task 6: Implement Session Refresh and Get\n138: **Verifiable Output:** Session activity tracking works correctly\n139: \n140: - [ ] Implement `Refresh()` method:\n141:   - Retrieve session from store\n142:   - Update LastActivity timestamp\n143:   - Extend ExpiresAt (capped at MaxTTL from creation)\n144:   - Update store entry\n145: - [ ] Implement `Get()` method:\n146:   - Retrieve session by ID\n147:   - Check expiration status\n148:   - Return ErrSessionExpired if expired\n149:   - Return ErrSessionNotFound if not exists\n150: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n151:   - Refresh updates activity and extends expiration\n152:   - Refresh returns ErrSessionNotFound for missing session\n153:   - Refresh returns ErrSessionExpired for expired session\n154:   - Get returns correct SessionInfo\n155:   - Get returns error for expired session\n156: \n157: **Verification Command:**\n158: ```bash\n159: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManager_Refresh|TestSessionManager_Get\"\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## Task 7: Implement Session Termination\n165: **Verifiable Output:** Clean session cleanup with store and Workload Manager\n166: \n167: - [ ] Implement `Terminate()` method:\n168:   - Mark session as terminating in affinity router\n169:   - Delete session from store\n170:   - Call Workload Manager to delete sandbox\n171:   - Unregister from affinity router\n172:   - Record metrics (activeSessions.Dec())\n173: - [ ] Implement `ListActive()` method with filter support\n174: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n175:   - Successful termination flow\n176:   - Store delete failure handling\n177:   - Workload Manager failure handling\n178:   - ListActive with various filters\n179: \n180: **Verification Command:**\n181: ```bash\n182: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManager_Terminate|TestSessionManager_ListActive\"\n183: ```\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## Task 8: Create Session Resolver\n188: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_resolver.go` with caching and fallback\n189: \n190: - [ ] Create `session_resolver.go` file\n191: - [ ] Define `SessionResolver` interface with methods:\n192:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n193:   - `WarmCache(ctx, namespace) error`\n194: - [ ] Implement `sessionResolver` struct with store client and k8s client fields\n195: - [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySession()`:\n196:   - Query session store first\n197:   - On cache miss, query K8s resource via client-go\n198:   - Cache result if found\n199:   - Return appropriate errors\n200: - [ ] Implement `WarmCache()` for preloading\n201: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n202:   - Cache hit scenario\n203:   - Cache miss with K8s fallback\n204:   - K8s resource not found\n205:   - Cache warming functionality\n206: \n207: **Verification Command:**\n208: ```bash\n209: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionResolver\"\n210: ```\n211: \n212: ---\n213: \n214: ## Task 9: Create Affinity Router\n215: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_affinity.go` with sticky routing\n216: \n217: - [ ] Create `session_affinity.go` file\n218: - [ ] Define `AffinityRouter` struct with sessionIndex map and RWMutex\n219: - [ ] Implement `NewAffinityRouter()` constructor\n220: - [ ] Implement `GetEndpoint(sessionID)`:\n221:   - Returns EndpointEntry and found boolean\n222:   - Updates LastUsed timestamp\n223: - [ ] Implement `RegisterSession(sessionInfo)`:\n224:   - Adds session to index with endpoint from EntryPoints\n225: - [ ] Implement `UnregisterSession(sessionID)`:\n226:   - Removes session from index\n227: - [ ] Implement `HealthCheck(sessionID, healthy)`:\n228:   - Updates endpoint health status\n229: - [ ] Implement thread-safe operations with RWMutex\n230: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n231:   - Register and retrieve session\n232:   - Unregister removes session\n233:   - Concurrent access safety\n234:   - Health check updates status\n235: \n236: **Verification Command:**\n237: ```bash\n238: go test ./pkg/router/... -race -v -run \"TestAffinityRouter\"\n239: ```\n240: \n241: ---\n242: \n243: ## Task 10: Create Kubernetes Runtime Client\n244: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/k8s_client.go` with client-go wrapper\n245: \n246: - [ ] Create `k8s_client.go` file\n247: - [ ] Define `RuntimeClient` struct with client-go interface fields\n248: - [ ] Implement `NewRuntimeClient(config *rest.Config) (*RuntimeClient, error)`\n249: - [ ] Implement `GetAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name)` using runtimev1alpha1 client\n250: - [ ] Implement `GetCodeInterpreter(ctx, namespace, name)` using runtimev1alpha1 client\n251: - [ ] Implement `WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace)` returning watch.Interface\n252: - [ ] Implement `WatchCodeInterpreters(ctx, namespace)` returning watch.Interface\n253: - [ ] Implement `ResolveRuntime(ctx, ref RuntimeReference)` returning RuntimeConfig\n254: - [ ] Add error mapping from K8s API errors to session errors\n255: - [ ] Write unit tests with fake client:\n256:   - Get existing AgentRuntime\n257:   - Get non-existent resource\n258:   - Watch operations\n259:   - Error mapping\n260: \n261: **Verification Command:**\n262: ```bash\n263: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestRuntimeClient\"\n264: ```\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ## Task 11: Create Session Lifecycle Manager\n269: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_lifecycle.go` with background maintenance\n270: \n271: - [ ] Create `session_lifecycle.go` file\n272: - [ ] Implement `StartLifecycleManager(stopCh)`:\n273:   - Start cleanup ticker with CleanupInterval\n274:   - Listen for stop signal\n275: - [ ] Implement `cleanupExpiredSessions(ctx)`:\n276:   - Call store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, time.Now(), batchSize)\n277:   - For each expired sandbox, call Terminate()\n278:   - Record metrics for expired sessions\n279:   - Log errors but continue processing\n280: - [ ] Implement `cleanupInactiveSessions(ctx)` (optional enhancement):\n281:   - Identify sessions with LastActivity > ActivityTimeout\n282:   - Mark for expiration or terminate\n283: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n284:   - Lifecycle manager starts and stops correctly\n285:   - Expired sessions are cleaned up\n286:   - Cleanup errors are handled gracefully\n287: \n288: **Verification Command:**\n289: ```bash\n290: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestLifecycleManager\"\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Task 12: Create Session Metrics\n296: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_metrics.go` with Prometheus metrics\n297: \n298: - [ ] Create `session_metrics.go` file\n299: - [ ] Define Prometheus metrics:\n300:   - `agentcube_session_creations_total` (CounterVec with labels: kind, result)\n301:   - `agentcube_active_sessions` (Gauge)\n302:   - `agentcube_sessions_expired_total` (Counter)\n303:   - `agentcube_session_resolve_duration_seconds` (HistogramVec with labels: cache_hit)\n304:   - `agentcube_session_duration_seconds` (Histogram)\n305:   - `agentcube_affinity_route_hits_total` (CounterVec with labels: result)\n306: - [ ] Implement `sessionMetrics` struct with all metric collectors\n307: - [ ] Implement `NewSessionMetrics() *sessionMetrics`\n308: - [ ] Implement recording methods for each metric\n309: - [ ] Implement `RegisterMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer)`\n310: - [ ] Write unit tests verifying metrics registration\n311: \n312: **Verification Command:**\n313: ```bash\n314: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionMetrics\"\n315: ```\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ## Task 13: Implement JWT Manager\n320: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt.go` with RSA-signed JWT generation\n321: \n322: - [ ] Review and extend existing `jwt.go` if present, or create new\n323: - [ ] Define `JWTManager` struct with privateKey, publicKey, clientset fields\n324: - [ ] Implement `NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)`\n325: - [ ] Implement `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)`:\n326:   - Include standard claims: exp, iat, iss=\"agentcube-router\"\n327:   - Sign with RSA private key\n328: - [ ] Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`:\n329:   - Check for existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n330:   - If not exists, generate RSA key pair\n331:   - Store keys in Kubernetes Secret\n332:   - Load keys from Secret if exists\n333: - [ ] Implement `ValidateToken(token string) (map[string]interface{}, error)`\n334: - [ ] Write unit tests:\n335:   - Token generation with session claims\n336:   - Token validation\n337:   - Expiration enforcement\n338:   - Secret storage and retrieval\n339: \n340: **Verification Command:**\n341: ```bash\n342: go test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTManager\"\n343: ```\n344: \n345: ---\n346: \n347: ## Task 14: Create HTTP Handlers for Session Management\n348: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/handlers.go` with session-aware HTTP handlers\n349: \n350: - [ ] Review existing handlers from AR-009\n351: - [ ] Add session resolution middleware:\n352:   - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n353:   - Call SessionManager.Resolve()\n354:   - Store session info in context\n355: - [ ] Implement session injection in response headers