{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862814354,"sessionID":"ses_28656b9f8ffeB7yx0UgDfwYzlW","part":{"id":"prt_d79a9e0350018L9Ai0FpAQdorY","messageID":"msg_d79a9c857001O5Rjbnxyujdfec","sessionID":"ses_28656b9f8ffeB7yx0UgDfwYzlW","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","content":"# AR-011: Router JWT и®ӨиҜҒдёҺзӯҫеҸ‘ - Task Checklist\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-011  \n> **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 completed  \n> **Depends on:** AR-009 (Router HTTP Core), AR-010 (Session Management)\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Create JWT Types and Constants\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_types.go` with core type definitions\n\n- [ ] Create `jwt_types.go` file\n- [ ] Define `TokenClaims` struct with fields:\n  - `SessionID string` - Session identifier\n  - `UserID string` - User identifier (optional)\n  - `SandboxID string` - Associated sandbox ID\n  - `Namespace string` - Kubernetes namespace\n  - `RuntimeKind string` - Runtime type (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n- [ ] Define `TokenPair` struct with `AccessToken` and `RefreshToken` fields\n- [ ] Define `TokenMetadata` struct with `IssuedAt`, `ExpiresAt`, `RefreshExpiresAt` fields\n- [ ] Define JWT constants:\n  - `TokenIssuer = \"agentcube-router\"`\n  - `AccessTokenExpiry = 5 * time.Minute`\n  - `RefreshTokenExpiry = 24 * time.Hour`\n  - `SecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n- [ ] Add JSON tags and documentation comments for all types\n- [ ] Write unit tests verifying type definitions and constants\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTTypes\" && \\\ngrep -E \"TokenClaims|TokenPair|TokenMetadata\" pkg/router/jwt_types.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Create JWT Error Types\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_errors.go` with error definitions\n\n- [ ] Create `jwt_errors.go` file (if not exists)\n- [ ] Define `JWTError` struct with Code, Message, Cause fields\n- [ ] Implement `Error() string` method\n- [ ] Implement `Unwrap() error` method\n- [ ] Define sentinel errors:\n  - `ErrTokenExpired` (code: TOKEN_EXPIRED)\n  - `ErrTokenInvalid` (code: TOKEN_INVALID)\n  - `ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` (code: TOKEN_SIGNATURE_INVALID)\n  - `ErrTokenMalformed` (code: TOKEN_MALFORMED)\n  - `ErrKeyNotFound` (code: KEY_NOT_FOUND)\n  - `ErrKeyGenerationFailed` (code: KEY_GENERATION_FAILED)\n  - `ErrSecretAccessFailed` (code: SECRET_ACCESS_FAILED)\n- [ ] Write unit tests verifying error creation and unwrapping\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTError\" && \\\ngrep \"ErrTokenExpired\\|ErrTokenInvalid\" pkg/router/jwt_errors.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Extend JWT Manager with Validation\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt.go` with token validation methods\n\n- [ ] Implement `ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*TokenClaims, error)`:\n  - Parse JWT with RS256 signing method\n  - Verify signature using public key\n  - Extract and validate standard claims (exp, iat, iss)\n  - Extract custom claims (session_id, sandbox_id, etc.)\n  - Return `*TokenClaims` on success\n  - Return appropriate errors on failure\n- [ ] Implement `parseTokenClaims(claims jwt.MapClaims) (*TokenClaims, error)`:\n  - Extract session_id claim\n  - Extract sandbox_id claim\n  - Extract namespace claim\n  - Extract runtime_kind claim\n  - Validate required fields\n- [ ] Add context-aware validation method `ValidateTokenWithContext(ctx, token)`\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Valid token validation succeeds\n  - Expired token returns ErrTokenExpired\n  - Invalid signature returns ErrTokenSignatureInvalid\n  - Malformed token returns ErrTokenMalformed\n  - Missing claims returns appropriate error\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTManager_Validate\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: Implement Token Refresh Mechanism\n**Verifiable Output:** Token refresh functionality in JWTManager\n\n- [ ] Implement `GenerateTokenPair(claims map[string]interface{}) (*TokenPair, *TokenMetadata, error)`:\n  - Generate access token with 5-minute expiry\n  - Generate refresh token with 24-hour expiry\n  - Include jti (JWT ID) claim for refresh token tracking\n  - Return both tokens with metadata\n- [ ] Implement `RefreshToken(refreshToken string) (*TokenPair, *TokenMetadata, error)`:\n  - Validate refresh token signature and expiry\n  - Extract original claims\n  - Generate new token pair\n  - Return new access and refresh tokens\n- [ ] Implement refresh token rotation (optional security enhancement)\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Token pair generation succeeds\n  - Refresh token generates new valid pair\n  - Expired refresh token returns error\n  - Invalid refresh token returns error\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTManager_Refresh\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: Create JWT Configuration Types\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_config.go` with configuration types\n\n- [ ] Create `jwt_config.go` file\n- [ ] Define `JWTConfig` struct with fields:\n  - `AccessTokenExpiry time.Duration`\n  - `RefreshTokenExpiry time.Duration`\n  - `RSAKeySize int` (default: 2048)\n  - `Issuer string`\n  - `SecretName string`\n  - `SecretNamespace string`\n- [ ] Implement `DefaultJWTConfig()` returning default configuration\n- [ ] Implement `JWTConfig.Validate()` method:\n  - Validate AccessTokenExpiry > 0\n  - Validate RefreshTokenExpiry > AccessTokenExpiry\n  - Validate RSAKeySize >= 2048\n  - Validate Issuer is not empty\n- [ ] Add environment variable support:\n  - `AGENTCUBE_JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY`\n  - `AGENTCUBE_JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRY`\n  - `AGENTCUBE_JWT_SECRET_NAME`\n- [ ] Write unit tests for configuration validation\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTConfig\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 6: Implement JWT Middleware\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go` with HTTP middleware\n\n- [ ] Create `jwt_middleware.go` file\n- [ ] Define `JWTMiddleware` struct with JWTManager field\n- [ ] Implement `NewJWTMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager) *JWTMiddleware`\n- [ ] Implement `Authenticate(next http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n  - Extract Authorization header (Bearer token)\n  - Validate token using JWTManager\n  - Store TokenClaims in request context\n  - Call next handler on success\n  - Return 401 on authentication failure\n- [ ] Implement `OptionalAuthenticate(next http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n  - Authenticate if token present\n  - Allow request through if no token\n- [ ] Implement `RequireSession(next http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n  - Verify session_id claim exists\n  - Verify session is valid (call session manager)\n  - Return 401 if session invalid\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Valid token passes authentication\n  - Missing token returns 401\n  - Invalid token returns 401\n  - Expired token returns 401\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTMiddleware\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 7: Create JWT HTTP Handlers\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_handlers.go` with HTTP endpoints\n\n- [ ] Create `jwt_handlers.go` file\n- [ ] Implement `handleTokenGenerate(w, r)`:\n  - Accept POST with claims in body\n  - Validate request body\n  - Generate token pair via JWTManager\n  - Return 200 with tokens JSON\n  - Return 400 on invalid request\n- [ ] Implement `handleTokenRefresh(w, r)`:\n  - Accept POST with refresh_token in body\n  - Validate refresh token\n  - Generate new token pair\n  - Return 200 with new tokens\n  - Return 401 on invalid/expired refresh token\n- [ ] Implement `handlePublicKey(w, r)`:\n  - Return 200 with public key in PEM format\n  - Used by clients to validate tokens\n- [ ] Implement `handleTokenValidate(w, r)`:\n  - Accept POST with token in body\n  - Return 200 with token claims if valid\n  - Return 401 if invalid\n- [ ] Add proper request/response DTOs with JSON tags\n- [ ] Write unit tests for all handlers\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTHandlers\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 8: Integrate JWT with Session Manager\n**Verifiable Output:** Session-aware JWT token generation\n\n- [ ] Extend session manager to use JWT:\n  - Add `GenerateSessionToken(sessionID string) (*TokenPair, error)`\n  - Add `ValidateSessionToken(token string) (*SessionInfo, error)`\n- [ ] Implement session claims injection:\n  - session_id from SessionInfo.SessionID\n  - sandbox_id from SessionInfo.SandboxID\n  - namespace from SessionInfo.Namespace\n  - runtime_kind from SessionInfo.RuntimeRef.Kind\n- [ ] Add session validation to JWT middleware:\n  - Extract session_id from token\n  - Verify session exists via SessionManager\n  - Verify session is active\n- [ ] Write integration tests:\n  - Token generation for active session succeeds\n  - Token validation with valid session succeeds\n  - Token validation with terminated session fails\n  - Token validation with expired session fails\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTSessionIntegration\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 9: Add JWT Metrics\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_metrics.go` with Prometheus metrics\n\n- [ ] Create `jwt_metrics.go` file\n- [ ] Define Prometheus metrics:\n  - `agentcube_jwt_tokens_generated_total` (CounterVec with labels: type)\n  - `agentcube_jwt_tokens_validated_total` (CounterVec with labels: result)\n  - `agentcube_jwt_validations_failed_total` (CounterVec with labels: reason)\n  - `agentcube_jwt_validation_duration_seconds` (Histogram)\n  - `agentcube_jwt_active_refresh_tokens` (Gauge)\n- [ ] Implement `jwtMetrics` struct with all collectors\n- [ ] Implement `NewJWTMetrics() *jwtMetrics`\n- [ ] Implement recording methods for each metric\n- [ ] Wire metrics into JWTManager methods\n- [ ] Write unit tests verifying metrics registration\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTMetrics\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 10: Enhance Kubernetes Secret Management\n**Verifiable Output:** Robust secret handling with rotation support\n\n- [ ] Implement `RotateKeys(ctx context.Context) error`:\n  - Generate new RSA key pair\n  - Store new keys in secret with version annotation\n  - Keep old keys for token validation during transition\n  - Update JWTManager with new keys\n- [ ] Implement key versioning in secrets:\n  - Add `key-version` annotation\n  - Add `key-created-at` annotation\n  - Support multiple key versions\n- [ ] Implement graceful key rotation:\n  - Sign new tokens with new key\n  - Validate tokens with any active key\n  - Remove old keys after transition period\n- [ ] Add context support to secret operations:\n  - Update `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n  - Update `createOrLoadSecret(ctx)`\n  - Update `loadExistingSecret(ctx)`\n- [ ] Write unit tests with mock Kubernetes client:\n  - Key rotation succeeds\n  - Token signed with old key validates after rotation\n  - New tokens signed with new key\n  - Secret creation on first startup\n  - Secret loading on subsequent startups\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTKeyRotation\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 11: Create JWT Manager Interface\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt_manager.go` with clean interface\n\n- [ ] Create `jwt_manager.go` file (refactor from existing jwt.go)\n- [ ] Define `TokenManager` interface with methods:\n  - `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)`\n  - `GenerateTokenPair(claims map[string]interface{}) (*TokenPair, *TokenMetadata, error)`\n  - `ValidateToken(token string) (*TokenClaims, error)`\n  - `RefreshToken(refreshToken string) (*TokenPair, *TokenMetadata, error)`\n  - `GetPublicKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)`\n  - `Initialize(ctx context.Context) error`\n- [ ] Refactor existing `JWTManager` to implement interface\n- [